\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\cf1\b\f0\fs36 #\cf0 Food filter\par

\pard\li721\sa200\sl240\slmult1\qj\b0\f2\fs22 There is a TextBox above the Food DataGrid (in the <Food> tab). You type text into it and press the \{Enter\} key. As a result the DataGrid only displays those foods whose "Food Description" field contains that text. The TextBox is then cleared, with the filter text now displayed to its right and focus shifts to the now selected top row in the DataGrid. Sorting is ascending with respect to the <Id> field (internally called "FoodId"). Note: if the filter gives no results the focus remains in the TextBox.\line\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\cf1\b\f0\fs36 #\cf0 Food CheckBox\par

\pard\li721\sa200\sl240\slmult1\qj\b0\f2\fs22 There is one CheckBox above the Food DataGrid (in the <Food> tab). It is titled "Only show main columns".\par
When Unchecked the DataGrid displays all fields from the foods table.\par
When Checked a subset of nutritional information is displayed. In particular only the fields :\par

\pard\li720\sl240\slmult1\tab "FoodId"\par
\tab "FoodDescription"\par
\tab "Energy"\par
\tab "Protein"\par
\tab "FatTotal"\par
\tab "SaturatedFat"\par
\tab "Carbohydrate"\par
\tab "Sugars"\par
\tab "DietaryFibre"\par
\tab "SodiumNa"\par

\pard\li721\sl240\slmult1\par

